astActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n27:     Close() error\n28: }\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** õĖĆõĖ¬ÕüźÕ║ĘńÜä Redis/Valkey µ£ŹÕŖĪÕÖ©\n34: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `Ping(ctx)`\n35: - **THEN** Õ«×ńÄ░ÕÅæķĆü PING ÕæĮõ╗żÕ╣ČĶ”üµ▒éĶ┐öÕø×ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ `PONG`\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## ķöÖĶ»»ÕżäńÉå\n40: \n41: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n42: \n43: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Ķ┐öÕø×Õīģń║¦ķöÖĶ»» `ErrNotFound`’╝łµČłµü» `store: not found`’╝ē’╝īÕĮō session key Õ£©Ķ»╗ÕÅ¢µŚČõĖŹÕŁśÕ£©’╝īµł¢µ£ĆÕÉÄµ┤╗ÕŖ©µŚČķŚ┤µø┤µ¢░µīćÕÉæń╝║Õż▒ńÜä session µŚČŃĆé\n44: \n45: ```go\n46: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Scenario: Get missing session\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** ÕÉÄń½»õĖŹÕŁśÕ£© key `session:{id}`\n52: - **WHEN** µē¦ĶĪī `GetSandboxBySessionID`\n53: - **THEN** ķöÖĶ»»õĖ║ `ErrNotFound`’╝łRedis: `Nil`’╝øValkey: `IsValkeyNil`’╝ē\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## µĢ░µŹ«ÕŁśÕé©ķö«Ķ«ŠĶ«Ī\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n60: \n61: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL õĮ┐ńö©ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ÕēŹń╝Ć `session:` õĖÄ session id µŗ╝µÄźõĮ£õĖ║ JSON µ¢ćµĪŻÕŁśÕé©ńÜäõĖ╗ķö«ŃĆé\n62: \n63: ### Scenario: Key construction\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n66: - **WHEN** ÕŁśÕé©ÕåÖÕģź sandbox µĢ░µŹ«\n67: - **THEN** ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ key õĖ║ `session:abc`\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: ## ń┤óÕ╝ĢĶ«ŠĶ«Ī\n72: \n73: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n74: \n75: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL ń╗┤µŖżµ£ēÕ║ÅķøåÕÉł key `session:expiry`’╝īµłÉÕæśõĖ║ session id’╝īÕłåµĢ░õĖ║ `ExpiresAt` Unix ń¦ÆµĢ░ŃĆé`StoreSandbox` SHALL µĘ╗ÕŖĀµłÉÕæśÕ╣ČõĮ┐ńö© sandbox Ķ┐ćµ£¤ÕłåµĢ░ŃĆé`DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ÕłĀķÖżµłÉÕæśŃĆé\n76: \n77: ### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` õĖö limit > 0\n80: - **WHEN** Õ«×ńÄ░µ¤źĶ»óń┤óÕ╝Ģ\n81: - **THEN** ķĆēµŗ®ÕłåµĢ░õ╗ÄĶ┤¤µŚĀń®ĘÕł░ `before.Unix()` ńÜäµłÉÕæś’╝īķÖÉÕłČõĖ║ `limit` µØĪ\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n84: \n85: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL ń╗┤µŖżµ£ēÕ║ÅķøåÕÉł key `session:last_activity`’╝īµłÉÕæśõĖ║ session id’╝īÕłåµĢ░õĖ║µ£ĆÕÉÄµ┤╗ÕŖ© Unix ń¦ÆµĢ░ŃĆé`StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD ÕłåµĢ░õĖ║ `time.Now().Unix()`ŃĆé`UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD µÅÉõŠøńÜäµŚČķŚ┤µł│’╝łµł¢ķøČµŚČõĮ┐ńö©ÕĮōÕēŹµŚČķŚ┤’╝ēŃĆé`DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM µłÉÕæśŃĆé\n86: \n87: ### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n88: \n89: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n90: - **WHEN** µē¦ĶĪī\n91: - **THEN** Ķ┐öÕø×µ£ĆÕÉÄµ┤╗ÕŖ©ÕłåµĢ░ Ōēż `before.Unix()` ńÜäµłÉÕæś’╝īµ£ĆÕżÜ `limit` µØĪ\n92: \n93: ---\n94: \n95: ## ÕŁśÕé©µōŹõĮ£\n96: \n97: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n98: \n99: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL µŗÆń╗Ø nil sandbox µł¢ķøČ `ExpiresAt`ŃĆéń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Õ£©õĖĆõĖ¬ pipeline/multi ÕØŚõĖŁµē¦ĶĪī session key ńÜä SETNXŃĆüZADD expiry ÕÆī ZADD last_activityŃĆéń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Õ”éµ×£µē╣ÕżäńÉåõĖŁõ╗╗õĮĢÕæĮõ╗żķöÖĶ»»ÕłÖÕż▒Ķ┤źŃĆé\n100: \n101: ### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n102: \n103: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n104: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö©\n105: - **THEN** ķöÖĶ»»µīćńż║ sandbox õĖ║ nil\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ## µø┤µ¢░µōŹõĮ£\n110: \n111: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n112: \n113: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL õ╗ģõĮ┐ńö© SET with XX’╝łkey Õ┐ģķĪ╗ÕŁśÕ£©’╝ēµø┤µ¢░ session JSON ÕĆ╝ŃĆéń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Õ£©µŁżµōŹõĮ£õĖŁõĖŹõ┐«µö╣ expiry µł¢ last-activity ZSET µØĪńø«ŃĆé\n114: \n115: ### Scenario: Missing key on update\n116: \n117: - **GIVEN** session key õĖŹÕŁśÕ£©\n118: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` Ķ┐ÉĶĪī\n119: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX Ķ┐öÕø× false ŌåÆ ķöÖĶ»» `key not exists`’╝øValkey: ÕōŹÕ║öķØ× OK ŌåÆ ÕÉīń▒╗ķöÖĶ»»\n120: \n121: ---\n122: \n123: ## ÕłĀķÖżµōŹõĮ£\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n126: \n127: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Õ£©õĖĆõĖ¬ pipeline/multi õĖŁÕłĀķÖż session key Õ╣Čõ╗ÄõĖżõĖ¬µ£ēÕ║ÅķøåÕÉłõĖŁń¦╗ķÖż session idŃĆé\n128: \n129: ### Scenario: Full removal\n130: \n131: - **GIVEN** õĖĆõĖ¬ÕŁśÕ£©ńÜä session\n132: - **WHEN** ÕłĀķÖżµłÉÕŖ¤\n133: - **THEN** GET session key Ķ┐öÕø× not found’╝īZSET õĖŹÕåŹÕīģÕÉ½Ķ»źµłÉÕæś\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: ## µ¤źĶ»óµōŹõĮ£\n138: \n139: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n140: \n141: ÕĮōµīē ZSET ÕłŚÕć║Ķ┐öÕø× session id µŚČ’╝īń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL µīē id ÕŖĀĶĮĮ JSON’╝øÕ”éµ×£ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ key ń╝║Õż▒ SHALL ĶĘ│Ķ┐ćµØĪńø«’╝łRedis pipeline GET nil’╝īValkey MGET ń®║ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓’╝ēĶĆīõĖŹÕ»╝Ķć┤µĢ┤õĖ¬µē╣ÕżäńÉåÕż▒Ķ┤źŃĆé\n142: \n143: ### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n144: \n145: - **GIVEN** ZSET õĖŁńÜä session id µ▓Īµ£ēÕ»╣Õ║öńÜä hash/string ÕĆ╝\n146: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` Ķ┐ÉĶĪī\n147: - **THEN** Ķ»ź id õ╗ÄĶ┐öÕø×ńÜä slice õĖŁń£üńĢź\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ## µ┤╗ÕŖ©µø┤µ¢░\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n154: \n155: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL µŗÆń╗Øń®║ session idŃĆéÕ”éµ×£ `at` õĖ║ķøČµŚČķŚ┤’╝īń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL õĮ┐ńö© `time.Now()`ŃĆéń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Õ£© ZADD ÕēŹķ¬īĶ»ü session key ÕŁśÕ£©’╝øÕ”éµ×£õĖŹÕŁśÕ£© SHALL Ķ┐öÕø× `ErrNotFound`ŃĆé\n156: \n157: ### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** µ▓Īµ£ē `session:{id}` key\n160: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n161: - **THEN** Ķ┐öÕø× `ErrNotFound`\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## ÕÉÄń½»ķĆēµŗ®\n166: \n167: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n168: \n169: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL õĖŹÕī║ÕłåÕż¦Õ░ÅÕåÖĶ»╗ÕÅ¢ `STORE_TYPE`’╝øÕ”éµ×£µ£¬Ķ«ŠńĮ« SHALL ķ╗śĶ«żõĖ║ `redis`ŃĆéµö»µīüńÜäÕĆ╝ SHALL õĖ║ `redis` ÕÆī `valkey`’╝øõ╗╗õĮĢÕģČõ╗¢ÕĆ╝ SHALL Õ»╝Ķć┤ÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢Õż▒Ķ┤źŃĆé\n170: \n171: ```go\n172: const (\n173:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n174:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n175: )\n176: ```\n177: \n178: ### Scenario: Default redis\n179: \n180: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` µ£¬Ķ«ŠńĮ«\n181: - **WHEN** `Storage()` ķ”¢µ¼ĪÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢\n182: - **THEN** Redis Õ«×ńÄ░Ķó½µ×äķĆĀ\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## Redis ķģŹńĮ«\n187: \n188: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n189: \n190: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Ķ”üµ▒é `REDIS_ADDR`ŃĆéń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Ķ”üµ▒éķØ×ń®║ `REDIS_PASSWORD`’╝īķÖżķØ× `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` õĖŹÕī║ÕłåÕż¦Õ░ÅÕåÖĶ«ŠńĮ«õĖ║ falseŃĆé\n191: \n192: ### Scenario: Password required by default\n193: \n194: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` Ķ«ŠńĮ«õĖö `REDIS_PASSWORD` õĖ║ń®║õĖö `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` µ£¬Ķ«ŠńĮ«\n195: - **WHEN** Redis store ÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢\n196: - **THEN** ÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢Õż▒Ķ┤ź’╝īķöÖĶ»»µÅÉńż║ķ£ĆĶ”üÕ»åńĀü\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ## Valkey ķģŹńĮ«\n201: \n202: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n203: \n204: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Ķ”üµ▒é `VALKEY_ADDR`’╝łķĆŚÕÅĘÕłåķÜöńÜäÕ£░ÕØĆµŗåÕłåõĖ║ `InitAddress`’╝ēŃĆéń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Ķ”üµ▒éķØ×ń®║ `VALKEY_PASSWORD`’╝īķÖżķØ× `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`ŃĆéń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Õ£© `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` Ķ¦Żµ×ÉõĖ║ true µŚČĶ«ŠńĮ« `DisableCache` õĖ║ true’╝øń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL Õ£© `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` Ķ¦Żµ×ÉõĖ║ true µŚČĶ«ŠńĮ« `ForceSingleClient` õĖ║ trueŃĆé\n205: \n206: ### Scenario: Single address configuration\n207: \n208: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=localhost:7379`\n209: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` µ×äÕ╗║ķĆēķĪ╣\n210: - **THEN** `InitAddress` õĖ║ `[]string{\"localhost:7379\"}`\n211: \n212: ### Scenario: Multiple addresses configuration\n213: \n214: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=node1:7379,node2:7379,node3:7379`\n215: - **WHEN** `makeValkeyOptions()` µ×äÕ╗║ķĆēķĪ╣\n216: - **THEN** `InitAddress` õĖ║ `[]string{\"node1:7379\", \"node2:7379\", \"node3:7379\"}`\n217: \n218: ### Scenario: Password required by default\n219: \n220: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` Ķ«ŠńĮ«õĖö `VALKEY_PASSWORD` õĖ║ń®║õĖö `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` µ£¬Ķ«ŠńĮ«µł¢ķØ× \"false\"\n221: - **WHEN** Valkey Õ«óµłĘń½»ÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢\n222: - **THEN** ÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢Õż▒Ķ┤ź’╝īķöÖĶ»»µÅÉńż║ķ£ĆĶ”üÕ»åńĀü\n223: \n224: ### Scenario: Password optional when disabled\n225: \n226: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` Ķ«ŠńĮ«õĖö `VALKEY_PASSWORD` õĖ║ń®║õĖö `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n227: - **WHEN** Valkey Õ«óµłĘń½»ÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢\n228: - **THEN** Õ«óµłĘń½»ÕłøÕ╗║µŚČõĖŹõĮ┐ńö©Õ»åńĀü\n229: - **AND** `ClientOption.Password` õĖ║ń®║ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓\n230: \n231: ### Scenario: Password provided\n232: \n233: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD=secret123`\n234: - **WHEN** Valkey Õ«óµłĘń½»ÕłØÕ¦ŗÕī¢\n235: - **THEN** `ClientOption.Password` õĖ║ \"secret123\"\n236: \n237: ### Scenario: Optional client flags\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n240: - **WHEN** Valkey client options Ķó½µ×äÕ╗║\n241: - **THEN** `ClientOption` õĖŖńÜä `DisableCache` õĖ║ true\n242: \n243: ### Scenario: Disable cache not set\n244: \n245: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` µ£¬Ķ«ŠńĮ«\n246: - **WHEN** Valkey client options Ķó½µ×äÕ╗║\n247: - **THEN** `ClientOption.DisableCache` õĖ║ false’╝łķ╗śĶ«ż’╝ē\n248: \n249: ### Scenario: Force single client enabled\n250: \n251: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n252: - **WHEN** Valkey client options Ķó½µ×äÕ╗║\n253: - **THEN** `ClientOption.ForceSingleClient` õĖ║ true\n254: \n255: ### Scenario: Force single client not set\n256: \n257: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` µ£¬Ķ«ŠńĮ«\n258: - **WHEN** Valkey client options Ķó½µ×äÕ╗║\n259: - **THEN** `ClientOption.ForceSingleClient` õĖ║ false’╝łķ╗śĶ«ż’╝ē\n260: \n261: ---\n262: \n263: ## ÕŹĢõŠŗĶ«┐ķŚ«\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n266: \n267: ń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL õĮ┐ńö© `sync.Once` µÜ┤ķ£▓ `func Storage() Store`’╝øÕż▒Ķ┤źńÜä init SHALL ķĆÜĶ┐ć klog Ķ«░ÕĮĢ fatalŃĆé\n268: \n269: ```go\n270: func Storage() Store\n271: func initStore() error\n272: ```\n273: \n274: ### Scenario: Single initialization\n275: \n276: - **GIVEN** ÕżÜõĖ¬ goroutine Ķ░āńö© `Storage()`\n277: - **WHEN** Õ«āõ╗¼Õ╣ČÕÅæĶ┐ÉĶĪī\n278: - **THEN** `initStore` µü░ÕźĮµē¦ĶĪīõĖĆµ¼Ī\n279: \n280: ---\n281: \n282: ## ÕŁśÕé©ńÜäµĢ░µŹ«ń╗ōµ×ä\n283: \n284: ### SandboxInfo ń╗ōµ×äõĮō\n285: \n286: ```go\n287: type SandboxInfo struct {\n288:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n289:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n290:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n291:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n292:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n293:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n294:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n295:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n296:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n297: }\n298: \n299: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n300:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n301:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n302:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n303: }\n304: ```\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ## Redis Õ«×ńÄ░ń╗åĶŖé\n309: \n310: ### Requirement: RedisStore struct\n311: \n312: Redis Õ«×ńÄ░ SHALL õĮ┐ńö© `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` Õ«óµłĘń½»ŃĆé\n313: \n314: ```go\n315: type redisStore struct {\n316:     cli                  *redisv9.Client\n317:     sessionPrefix        string\n318:     expiryIndexKey       string\n319:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n320: }\n321: ```\n322: \n323: ### Requirement: Fixed key patterns\n324: \n325: | Field | Value |\n326: |-------|--------|\n327: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n328: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n329: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n330: \n331: ### Scenario: Redis operations summary\n332: \n333: | Method | Redis commands |\n334: |--------|----------------|\n335: | `Ping` | `PING` ŌåÆ expect `PONG` |\n336: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n337: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n338: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n339: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n340: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n341: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n342: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n343: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n344: \n345: ---\n346: \n347: ## Valkey Õ«×ńÄ░ń╗åĶŖé\n348: \n349: ### Requirement: ValkeyStore struct\n350: \n351: Valkey Õ«×ńÄ░ SHALL õĮ┐ńö© `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` Õ«óµłĘń½»ŃĆé\n352: \n353: ```go\n354: type valkeyStore struct {\n355:     cli                  valkey.Client\n356:     sessionPrefix        string\n357:     expiryIndexKey       string\n358:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n359: }\n360: ```\n361: \n362: ### Scenario: Valkey operations summary\n363: \n364: | Method | Valkey API |\n365: |--------|------------|\n366: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` ŌåÆ string `PONG` |\n367: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` ŌåÆ bytes; `IsValkeyNil` ŌåÆ `ErrNotFound` |\n368: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n369: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n370: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n371: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n372: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n373: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key ŌåÆ int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n374: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n375: \n376: ### Scenario: Successful ping\n377: \n378: - **GIVEN** õĖĆõĖ¬ÕüźÕ║ĘńÜä Valkey µ£ŹÕŖĪÕÖ©\n379: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `Ping(ctx)`\n380: - **THEN** `B().Ping()` Ķó½µē¦ĶĪī\n381: - **AND** ń╗ōµ×£ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ńŁēõ║Ä \"PONG\"\n382: - **AND** error õĖ║ nil\n383: \n384: ### Scenario: Ping connection failure\n385: \n386: - **GIVEN** Valkey µ£ŹÕŖĪÕÖ©õĖŹÕÅ»ĶŠŠ\n387: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `Ping(ctx)`\n388: - **THEN** Ķ┐öÕø×µØźĶć¬ Valkey Õ«óµłĘń½»ńÜäķöÖĶ»»\n389: \n390: ### Scenario: Retrieve existing session\n391: \n392: - **GIVEN** key `session:abc` ÕŁśÕ£©õĖöÕīģÕÉ½µ£ēµĢł JSON\n393: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")`\n394: - **THEN** `B().Get().Key(\"session:abc\")` Ķ┐öÕø× JSON bytes\n395: - **AND** JSON unmarshals Õł░ `*types.SandboxInfo`\n396: - **AND** error õĖ║ nil\n397: \n398: ### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n399: \n400: - **GIVEN** key `session:xyz` õĖŹÕŁśÕ£©\n401: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"xyz\")`\n402: - **THEN** `B().Get()` Ķ┐öÕø× bytes õĖö `IsValkeyNil` õĖ║ true\n403: - **AND** error õĖ║ `ErrNotFound`\n404: \n405: ### Scenario: Successful store with all operations\n406: \n407: - **GIVEN** µ£ēµĢłńÜä `SandboxInfo` õĖö `ExpiresAt` ķØ×ķøČ\n408: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)`\n409: - **THEN** `DoMulti` µīēķĪ║Õ║Åµē¦ĶĪī’╝Ü\n410:   - `SETNX session:{id} {json}`\n411:   - `ZADD session:expiry {ExpiresAt.Unix()} {id}`\n412:   - `ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} {id}`\n413: - **AND** error õĖ║ nil\n414: \n415: ### Scenario: Pipeline operation fails\n416: \n417: - **GIVEN** DoMulti µ£¤ķŚ┤ Valkey Ķ┐×µÄźÕż▒Ķ┤ź\n418: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)`\n419: - **THEN** Ķ┐öÕø×µØźĶć¬ Valkey Õ«óµłĘń½»ńÜäķöÖĶ»»\n420: - **AND** µ▓Īµ£ēķā©ÕłåÕåÖÕģźĶó½µÅÉõ║ż\n421: \n422: ### Scenario: Update existing session\n423: \n424: - **GIVEN** key `session:abc` ÕŁśÕ£©\n425: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `UpdateSandbox(ctx, updated)`\n426: - **THEN** `SET session:abc {json} XX` Ķó½µē¦ĶĪī\n427: - **AND** `ToString()` ń╗ōµ×£ńŁēõ║Ä \"OK\"\n428: - **AND** error õĖ║ nil\n429: \n430: ### Scenario: Update missing session fails\n431: \n432: - **GIVEN** key `session:xyz` õĖŹÕŁśÕ£©\n433: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `UpdateSandbox(ctx, updated)`\n434: - **THEN** `SET ... XX` õĖŹõ╝ÜÕłøÕ╗║ key\n435: - **AND** `ToString()` ń╗ōµ×£õĖŹµś» \"OK\"\n436: - **AND** error µīćńż║ key õĖŹÕŁśÕ£©\n437: \n438: ### Scenario: List with limit > 0\n439: \n440: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 100)`\n441: - **AND** `before.Unix()` = 1710000000\n442: - **WHEN** µ¢╣µ│Ģµē¦ĶĪī\n443: - **THEN** Õ£© `session:expiry` õĖŖĶ░āńö© `Zrangebyscore`\n444: - **AND** `Min(\"-inf\")` ÕÆī `Max(\"1710000000\")`\n445: - **AND** Õ║öńö© `Limit(0, 100)`\n446: - **AND** ķĆÜĶ┐ć `Mget` ĶÄĘÕÅ¢µēĆµ£ēĶ┐öÕø×ńÜä session ID\n447: - **AND** µ£ēµĢłńÜä JSON µ¢ćµĪŻĶó½ unmarshal\n448: \n449: ### Scenario: List with limit <= 0 returns nil\n450: \n451: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)`\n452: - **WHEN** µ¢╣µ│Ģµē¦ĶĪī\n453: - **THEN** µ▓Īµ£ēµē¦ĶĪī Valkey µōŹõĮ£\n454: - **AND** ń╗ōµ×£õĖ║ `nil, nil`\n455: \n456: ### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n457: \n458: - **GIVEN** ZSET ÕīģÕÉ½ session id `orphan`\n459: - **AND** key `session:orphan` õĖŹÕŁśÕ£©\n460: - **WHEN** `Mget` õĖ║Ķ»ź key Ķ┐öÕø×ń®║\n461: - **THEN** `orphan` õ╗Äń╗ōµ×£ slice õĖŁń£üńĢź\n462: - **AND** ÕģČõ╗¢µ£ēµĢłńÜä session Ķó½ÕīģÕÉ½\n463: \n464: ### Scenario: Activity bump for existing session\n465: \n466: - **GIVEN** key `session:abc` ÕŁśÕ£©\n467: - **AND** `at` = 2024-04-10T12:00:00Z\n468: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at)`\n469: - **THEN** `Exists().Key(\"session:abc\")` Ķ┐öÕø× 1\n470: - **AND** `Zadd session:last_activity {at.Unix()} abc` Ķó½µē¦ĶĪī\n471: - **AND** error õĖ║ nil\n472: \n473: ### Scenario: Activity bump for missing session returns ErrNotFound\n474: \n475: - **GIVEN** key `session:xyz` õĖŹÕŁśÕ£©\n476: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"xyz\", at)`\n477: - **THEN** `Exists()` Ķ┐öÕø× 0\n478: - **AND** `Zadd` µ£¬µē¦ĶĪī\n479: - **AND** error õĖ║ `ErrNotFound`\n480: \n481: ### Scenario: Zero time uses current time\n482: \n483: - **GIVEN** ÕŁśÕ£©ńÜä session `abc`\n484: - **AND** `at.IsZero()` õĖ║ true\n485: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at)`\n486: - **THEN** `Zadd` ÕłåµĢ░õĮ┐ńö© `time.Now().Unix()`\n487: \n488: ### Scenario: Successful close\n489: \n490: - **GIVEN** µēōÕ╝ĆńÜä Valkey Õ«óµłĘń½»\n491: - **WHEN** Ķ░āńö© `Close()`\n492: - **THEN** `vs.cli.Close()` Ķó½µē¦ĶĪī\n493: - **AND** error õĖ║ nil\n494: \n495: ---\n496: \n497: ## õŠØĶĄ¢ķĪ╣\n498: \n499: ### Requirement: Package imports\n500: \n501: ```go\n502: import (\n503:     \"context\"\n504:     \"time\"\n505:     \"sync\"\n506: \n507:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n508:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n509:     \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n510:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n511: )\n512: ```\n513: \n514: ---\n515: \n516: ## Redis ÕÆī Valkey Õ«×ńÄ░ńÜäÕĘ«Õ╝é\n517: \n518: | µ¢╣ķØó | Redis | Valkey |\n519: |------|-------|--------|\n520: | Õ«óµłĘń½»Õ║ō | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` |\n521: | Ping µ¢╣µ│Ģ | `Ping(ctx)` ķĆÜĶ┐ćÕæĮõ╗żń╗ōµ×£Ķ┐öÕø× `PONG` | `B().Ping()` Ķ┐öÕø×ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ |\n522: | Get nil µŻĆµĄŗ | `redis.Nil` ķöÖĶ»» | Õ£© bytes ń╗ōµ×£õĖŖĶ░āńö© `IsValkeyNil()` |\n523: | Pipeline/Multi | `cli.Pipeline()` µł¢ `TxPipeline()` | `DoMulti()` µē¦ĶĪīÕżÜõĖ¬ÕæĮõ╗ż |\n524: | SETXX µłÉÕŖ¤µŻĆµ¤ź | Boolean ń╗ōµ×£ | `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n525: | ZRANGEBYSCORE | ÕĖ”µ£ē `RangeBy` ķĆēķĪ╣ńÜäÕ«óµłĘń½»µ¢╣µ│Ģ | `Zrangebyscore` ÕĖ”µ£ē `Min()`, `Max()`, `Limit()` |\n526: | µē╣ķćÅ GET | `cli.MGet(keys)` | `Mget(keys)` |\n527: | Key ÕŁśÕ£©µĆ¦ | `cli.Exists(ctx, key)` | `Exists().Key(key)` |\n528: | Õ£░ÕØĆķģŹńĮ« | ÕŹĢõĖ¬ `Addr` ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ | `InitAddress` ÕŁŚń¼”õĖ▓ slice |\n529: | ÕÅ»ķĆēµĀćÕ┐Ś | µŚĀ | `DisableCache`, `ForceSingleClient` |\n530: | Ķ┐×µÄźķĆēķĪ╣ | `redis.Options` ń╗ōµ×ä | `valkey.ClientOption` ń╗ōµ×ä |\n\n(End of file - total 530 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# delta-spec.md ŌĆö AR-014: Valkey ÕŁśÕé©Õ«×ńÄ░\n\n## Package: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nµ¢░Õó× Valkey ÕÉÄń½»Õ«×ńÄ░’╝īõĖÄ Redis ÕÉÄń½»Õ╣ČÕŁś’╝īńö©õ║Äµīüõ╣ģÕī¢ sandbox ÕģāµĢ░µŹ«ŃĆéµö»µīüµīē session ID ÕŁśÕé©ŃĆüµŻĆń┤óŃĆüµø┤µ¢░ÕÆīÕłĀķÖż’╝īÕ╣ČµÅÉõŠøÕ¤║õ║ÄĶ┐ćµ£¤µŚČķŚ┤ÕÆīµ£ĆÕÉÄµ┤╗ÕŖ©µŚČķŚ┤ńÜäń┤óÕ╝Ģµ¤źĶ»óŃĆéValkey Õ«×ńÄ░õĮ┐ńö© `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` Õ«óµłĘń½»Õ║ōŃĆé\n\n---\n\n## µ¢░Õó×µÄźÕÅŻÕÆīń▒╗Õ×ŗ\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\n\nń│╗ń╗¤ SHALL µÅÉõŠø `Store` µÄźÕÅŻ’╝īńö▒ Redis ÕÆī Valkey µÅÉõŠøÕĢåÕ«×ńÄ░ŃĆéValkey Õ«×ńÄ░õĮ┐ńö© `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` Õ«óµłĘń½»Õ║ōŃĆé\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863105774,"end":1775863105782}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775863105810,"sessionID":"ses_286502e0bffeC6f24MkVE13lqN","part":{"id":"prt_d79b088f8001UdXsTNcCpYiGy3","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79b08234001w9VSuv0Mj5zbJI","sessionID":"ses_286502e0bffeC6f24MkVE13lqN","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":22339,"input":184,"output":76,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":22079}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775863108875,"sessionID":"ses_286502e0bffeC6f24MkVE13lqN","part":{"id":"prt_d79b09509001aI6JJNuoH8GTPa","messageID":"msg_d79b089250017nV7WH5kLvw64n","sessionID":"ses_286502e0bffeC6f24MkVE13lqN","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863153940,"sessionID":"ses_286502e0bffeC6f24MkVE13lqN","part":{"id":"prt_d79b1448d001rGklpiZndM62d1","messageID":"msg_d79b089250017nV7WH5kLvw64n","sessionID":"ses_286502e0bffeC6f24MkVE13lqN","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-65555ab247684adbba2f49c9527b68a4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# delta-spec.md ŌĆö AR-019: CLI õ║īĶ┐øÕłČÕģźÕÅŻ\n\n## Module: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd`\n\n## Delta Overview\n\nAdd 4 CLI binary entry points to the cmd module for the agentcube project. These binaries provide command-line interfaces for interacting with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter Kubernetes resources via the client-go library.\n\n---\n\n## Binaries Overview\n\nThe following 4 binaries SHALL be provided:\n\n| Binary Name | Description | Package Path |\n|-------------|-------------|--------------|\n| `agentcube` | Main unified CLI with subcommands | `./cmd/agentcube` |\n| `agent-runtime` | Dedicated AgentRuntime resource management | `./cmd/agent-runtime` |\n| `code-interpreter` | Dedicated CodeInterpreter resource management | `./cmd/code-interpreter` |\n| `agentcube-util` | Utility commands: completion, validation, diagnostics | `./cmd/agentcube-util` |\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Main agentcube CLI binary\n\n### Requirement: Unified CLI entry point\n\nSystem SHALL provide a unified CLI entry point `agentcube` that aggregates subcommands for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Binary name: `agentcube`\n- Supports global flags for kubeconfig and namespace\n- Provides subcommands for runtime management\n- Provides subcommands for interpreter management\n- Outputs structured JSON/YAML when requested\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 1.1: Display help information\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube binary is installed\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube --help`\n- **THEN** the binary displays usage information\n- **AND** lists all available subcommands\n- **AND** shows global flags\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 1.2: Display version information\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube binary is installed\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube --version`\n- **THEN** the binary displays version information\n- **AND** includes git commit hash if available\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 1.3: Connect to Kubernetes cluster with custom kubeconfig\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube binary is installed\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube --kubeconfig=/path/to/kubeconfig runtime list`\n- **THEN** the binary uses the specified kubeconfig\n- **AND** successfully authenticates to the cluster\n- **AND** lists AgentRuntime resources\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 1.4: Use default namespace context\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube binary is installed\n- **AND** the user's kubecontext has a default namespace\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube runtime list`\n- **THEN** the binary queries resources in the default namespace\n- **AND** displays results\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 1.5: Override namespace with flag\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube binary is installed\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube --namespace=custom-ns runtime list`\n- **THEN** the binary queries resources in the 'custom-ns' namespace\n- **AND** displays results\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: AgentRuntime management CLI binary\n\n### Requirement: Dedicated CLI for AgentRuntime operations\n\nSystem SHALL provide a dedicated CLI `agent-runtime` for AgentRuntime resource operations with subcommands for create, get, list, update, delete, and watch.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Binary name: `agent-runtime` (accessible via `agentcube runtime` subcommand)\n- Supports CRUD operations on AgentRuntime resources\n- Supports watching resource changes\n- Validates input manifests before submission\n- Provides human-readable and machine-readable output formats\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 2.1: List AgentRuntime resources\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime list`\n- **THEN** the binary retrieves all AgentRuntime resources in the current namespace\n- **AND** displays them in tabular format\n- **AND** shows name, age, phase, and replicas columns\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.2: Get a specific AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with an AgentRuntime named 'test-runtime'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime get test-runtime`\n- **THEN** the binary retrieves the AgentRuntime\n- **AND** displays its full specification\n- **AND** includes status information\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.3: Create AgentRuntime from manifest file\n- **GIVEN** a valid AgentRuntime manifest file at './runtime.yaml'\n- **AND** the binary is configured with cluster access\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime create -f ./runtime.yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary validates the manifest\n- **AND** submits the resource to the API server\n- **AND** displays the created resource\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.4: Create AgentRuntime from stdin\n- **GIVEN** a valid AgentRuntime manifest\n- **AND** the binary is configured with cluster access\n- **WHEN** a user runs `cat runtime.yaml | agent-runtime create -f -`\n- **THEN** the binary reads from stdin\n- **AND** validates the manifest\n- **AND** submits the resource to the API server\n- **AND** displays the created resource\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.5: Update AgentRuntime from manifest\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named 'test-runtime'\n- **AND** a modified manifest file './updated-runtime.yaml'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime update -f ./updated-runtime.yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary retrieves the existing resource\n- **AND** applies the updates\n- **AND** submits to the API server\n- **AND** displays the updated resource\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.6: Delete AgentRuntime\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named 'test-runtime'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime delete test-runtime`\n- **THEN** the binary prompts for confirmation\n- **AND** upon confirmation, deletes the resource\n- **AND** displays success message\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.7: Delete AgentRuntime without confirmation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named 'test-runtime'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime delete test-runtime --force`\n- **THEN** the binary deletes the resource without confirmation\n- **AND** displays success message\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.8: Watch AgentRuntime changes\n- **GIVEN** the agent-runtime binary is running\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime watch`\n- **THEN** the binary streams real-time changes\n- **AND** displays added, modified, or deleted resources\n- **AND** continues until interrupted\n- **AND** exits with code 130 on SIGINT\n\n#### Scenario 2.9: Output JSON format\n- **GIVEN** the agent-runtime binary is configured\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime get test-runtime -o json`\n- **THEN** the binary outputs the resource in JSON format\n- **AND** the JSON is valid and parseable\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.10: Output YAML format\n- **GIVEN** the agent-runtime binary is configured\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime get test-runtime -o yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary outputs the resource in YAML format\n- **AND** the YAML is valid and parseable\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.11: List resources across all namespaces\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentRuntime resources in multiple namespaces\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime list --all-namespaces`\n- **THEN** the binary retrieves AgentRuntime resources from all namespaces\n- **AND** displays namespace as the first column\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 2.12: Filter resources by labels\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with labeled AgentRuntime resources\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agent-runtime list -l app=agentcube,env=prod`\n- **THEN** the binary filters resources by the specified labels\n- **AND** displays only matching resources\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: CodeInterpreter management CLI binary\n\n### Requirement: Dedicated CLI for CodeInterpreter operations\n\nSystem SHALL provide a dedicated CLI `code-interpreter` for CodeInterpreter resource operations with subcommands for create, get, list, update, delete, and watch.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Binary name: `code-interpreter` (accessible via `agentcube interpreter` subcommand)\n- Supports CRUD operations on CodeInterpreter resources\n- Supports watching resource changes\n- Validates input manifests before submission\n- Provides human-readable and machine-readable output formats\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 3.1: List CodeInterpreter resources\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with CodeInterpreter resources\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter list`\n- **THEN** the binary retrieves all CodeInterpreter resources in the current namespace\n- **AND** displays them in tabular format\n- **AND** shows name, age, runtime, and status columns\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 3.2: Get a specific CodeInterpreter\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with a CodeInterpreter named 'python-interpreter'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter get python-interpreter`\n- **THEN** the binary retrieves the CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** displays its full specification\n- **AND** includes status information\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 3.3: Create CodeInterpreter from manifest file\n- **GIVEN** a valid CodeInterpreter manifest file at './interpreter.yaml'\n- **AND** the binary is configured with cluster access\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter create -f ./interpreter.yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary validates the manifest\n- **AND** submits the resource to the API server\n- **AND** displays the created resource\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 3.4: Update CodeInterpreter from manifest\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named 'python-interpreter'\n- **AND** a modified manifest file './updated-interpreter.yaml'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter update -f ./updated-interpreter.yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary retrieves the existing resource\n- **AND** applies the updates\n- **AND** submits to the API server\n- **AND** displays the updated resource\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 3.5: Delete CodeInterpreter\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named 'python-interpreter'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter delete python-interpreter`\n- **THEN** the binary prompts for confirmation\n- **AND** upon confirmation, deletes the resource\n- **AND** displays success message\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 3.6: Watch CodeInterpreter changes\n- **GIVEN** the code-interpreter binary is running\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter watch`\n- **THEN** the binary streams real-time changes\n- **AND** displays added, modified, or deleted resources\n- **AND** continues until interrupted\n- **AND** exits with code 130 on SIGINT\n\n#### Scenario 3.7: Output JSON format\n- **GIVEN** the code-interpreter binary is configured\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter get python-interpreter -o json`\n- **THEN** the binary outputs the resource in JSON format\n- **AND** the JSON is valid and parseable\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 3.8: Filter by runtime type\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with CodeInterpreter resources of different types\n- **WHEN** a user runs `code-interpreter list --runtime python`\n- **THEN** the binary filters resources by the specified runtime type\n- **AND** displays only matching resources\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: Completion and utility binary\n\n### Requirement: Utility binary for shell completion and diagnostics\n\nSystem SHALL provide a utility binary `agentcube-util` providing shell completion generation, validation tools, and helper commands.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- Binary name: `agentcube-util` (or integrated into `agentcube util` subcommand)\n- Generates shell completion scripts for bash, zsh, fish, and powershell\n- Provides manifest validation without cluster connection\n- Provides dry-run mode for operations\n- Includes diagnostic commands for troubleshooting\n\n**Scenarios:**\n\n#### Scenario 4.1: Generate bash completion\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube-util binary is installed\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util completion bash`\n- **THEN** the binary outputs bash completion script\n- **AND** the script is syntactically valid\n- **AND** can be sourced by bash\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 4.2: Generate zsh completion\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube-util binary is installed\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util completion zsh`\n- **THEN** the binary outputs zsh completion script\n- **AND** the script is syntactically valid\n- **AND** can be sourced by zsh\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 4.3: Validate AgentRuntime manifest locally\n- **GIVEN** a manifest file at './runtime.yaml'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util validate -f ./runtime.yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary validates against the CRD schema\n- **AND** reports any validation errors\n- **AND** exits with code 0 if valid, code 1 if invalid\n\n#### Scenario 4.4: Validate CodeInterpreter manifest locally\n- **GIVEN** a manifest file at './interpreter.yaml'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util validate -f ./interpreter.yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary validates against the CRD schema\n- **AND** reports any validation errors\n- **AND** exits with code 0 if valid, code 1 if invalid\n\n#### Scenario 4.5: Validate directory of manifests\n- **GIVEN** a directory containing multiple manifest files at './manifests/'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util validate -f ./manifests/`\n- **THEN** the binary validates all YAML files in the directory\n- **AND** reports validation status for each file\n- **AND** exits with code 0 if all valid, code 1 if any invalid\n\n#### Scenario 4.6: Dry-run create operation\n- **GIVEN** a valid manifest file at './runtime.yaml'\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util dry-run -f ./runtime.yaml`\n- **THEN** the binary simulates the create operation\n- **AND** displays what would be created\n- **AND** does not modify cluster state\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n#### Scenario 4.7: Diagnose cluster connectivity\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube-util binary is installed\n- **AND** kubeconfig is configured\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util diagnose`\n- **THEN** the binary checks API server connectivity\n- **AND** checks authentication\n- **AND** checks CRD availability\n- **AND** displays diagnostic report\n- **AND** exits with code 0 if all checks pass\n\n#### Scenario 4.8: Show CRD information\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube-util binary is installed\n- **AND** connected to a cluster with agentcube CRDs\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube-util crd-info`\n- **THEN** the binary displays CRD versions\n- **AND** displays supported fields\n- **AND** displays validation schema\n- **AND** exits with code 0\n\n---\n\n## Integration Scenarios\n\n### INT-001: Subcommand delegation from main binary\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube main binary is installed\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube runtime list`\n- **THEN** the binary delegates to agent-runtime list\n- **AND** executes with same flags and arguments\n- **AND** returns same result as calling agent-runtime directly\n- **AND** exits with same code\n\n### INT-002: Shared configuration across binaries\n\n- **GIVEN** multiple agentcube binaries are installed\n- **AND** a kubeconfig file exists at ~/.kube/config\n- **WHEN** a user runs agent-runtime list AND code-interpreter list\n- **THEN** both binaries use the same kubeconfig\n- **AND** both use the same default namespace context\n- **AND** both authenticate with the same credentials\n\n### INT-003: Error handling with invalid kubeconfig\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube binary is installed\n- **AND** kubeconfig points to an inaccessible cluster\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube runtime list`\n- **THEN** the binary reports connection error\n- **AND** displays helpful error message\n- **AND** exits with code 1\n\n### INT-004: Graceful handling of missing CRDs\n\n- **GIVEN** the agentcube binary is installed\n- **AND** connected to a cluster without agentcube CRDs\n- **WHEN** a user runs `agentcube runtime list`\n- **THEN** the binary detects missing CRDs\n- **AND** displays informative message about CRD installation\n- **AND** exits with code 1\n\n---\n\n## Technical Constraints\n\n### Requirement: Language and toolchain\n\nSystem SHALL use Go 1.21+ and the following dependencies:\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` for API client\n- `k8s.io/client-go` for Kubernetes client libraries\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra` for CLI framework\n- `github.com/spf13/viper` for configuration management\n\n### Requirement: Build and installation\n\nEach binary SHALL be buildable independently via `go build ./cmd/<binary-name>`. Binaries SHALL be installable via `go install` from the repository root.\n\n### Requirement: Cross-platform support\n\nSystem SHALL support linux, darwin, windows architectures.\n\n### Requirement: Client-go integration\n\nSystem SHALL use the client-go library interfaces:\n- `runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInterface` for AgentRuntime operations\n- `runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInterface` for CodeInterpreter operations\n- REST resource plurals: `agentruntimes`, `codeinterpreters`\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\n\nSystem SHALL return appropriate exit codes:\n- Exit code 0 for successful operations\n- Exit code 1 for operation failures\n- Exit code 130 for SIGINT (Ctrl+C) interruption","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863153840,"end":1775863153937}}}}
